        <mxCell id="tQl9TI6B8Drq-oMKitGQ-240" value="&lt;b&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;A lot of these options are fairly self-explanatory, but the&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;DocConfig&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a bit more specific about documentation style: it is about Doxygen. So, the comment style prefers Doxygen-style formatted comments. For the languages that Doxygen doesn&#39;t support (e.g., Julia), common conventions are used." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;spacingLeft=10;spacingRight=10;" vertex="1" parent="WIyWlLk6GJQsqaUBKTNV-1">
